page.title: 13LANDSCAPE
page.content: THE CHURCH CENTRE,AN ALMOST UNALTERED EXAMPLE OF A VICTORIAN SCHOOL BUILT IN 1865 HOUSES A PLAYGROUP AND YOUTH CLUB.SUMMERS PLACE A VICTORIAN MANSION WAS PRIVATELY OWNED UNTIL 1946,WHEN IT BECAME THE IMMACULATE HEART OF MARY, CONVENT SCHOOL.THE INTERIOR REMAINED INTACT UNTIL 1984 WHEN SOTHEBY'S AUCTIONEERS ACQUIRED THE PROPERTY FOR DISPLAY AND AUCTION ROOMS.IN THE HIGH STREET ARE TIMBER FRAMED COTTAGES WITH HORSHAM STONE ROOFS.GUILDINGS,WYNSTRODE,AND COPPED HALL ARE EXAMPLES OF TUDOR TIMBER FRAMED FARM HOUSES STILL WITH EXPOSED BEAMS.THE LANDSCAPE RISES SLIGHTLY TO THE NORTH.IT IS MAINLY FARMLAND WITH GRAZING AND CROPS.IT IS DOTTED WITH SMALL DECIDUOUS COPSES.
